sentences: Original Concept was an American 1980s hip-hop group from Long Island, New York, United States, best known for their single “Can You Feel It.”
In the early 1980s, a group of young men at WBAU FM formed a group called the "Concept Crew."

Their show “The Operating Room” was broadcast on Monday nights from Adelphi University on the same station which featured the Spectrum City DJs (Chuck D and Flavor Flav) who later went on to form Public Enemy.
The members were Doctor Dré, T-Money, Rapper G, Easy G. By 1986, the group began calling themselves Original Concept and had released their first record, "Knowledge Me" in February of that year.
